 "mention": "TCDD", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9995380640029907, "span": {"begin": 1272, "end": 1276}}, {"id": ["mesh:C114895"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "PeCDF", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993847608566284, "span": {"begin": 1281, "end": 1286}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000013"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "bill deformities", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9998174905776978, "span": {"begin": 1301, "end": 1317}}, {"id": ["mesh:C536840"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "incomplete or lack of upper/lower beak", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9703218936920166, "span": {"begin": 1328, "end": 1366}}, {"id": ["mesh:D014190"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "crossbill", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.6196282505989075, "span": {"begin": 1370, "end": 1379}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:93934"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Japanese Quail", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.5013532638549805, "span": {"begin": 1412, "end": 1426}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4190", "285527"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "Ahr2 morpholino", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.7327694892883301, "span": {"begin": 1600, "end": 1615}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:7955"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "zebrafish", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9424211978912354, "span": {"begin": 1629, "end": 1638}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013749"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TCDD", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9994093179702759, "span": {"begin": 1660, "end": 1664}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013749"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TCDD", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9995482563972473, "span": {"begin": 1698, "end": 1702}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Ahr", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9924611449241638, "span": {"begin": 1759, "end": 1762}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9429747462272644, "span": {"begin": 1768, "end": 1772}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013749"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TCDD", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993988275527954, "span": {"begin": 1793, "end": 1797}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002972"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "cleft palate", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999551177024841, "span": {"begin": 1806, "end": 1818}}], "text": "Empirical evidence and essentiality of KEup for KEdown to occur  Some examples for empirical evidence from exposures to known Ahr activators:    TCDD exposure to developing mice causes cleft plate and negative effects on cell proliferation in the jaw region (Tao et al. 2020).     Beta-naphthoflavone (BNF) exposure to mink decreased squamous epithelial proliferation and caused lesions in mink jaws (Matz et al. 2019).       In zebrafish, PCB-126 exposure caused impaired lower jaw growth, and TCDD exposure decreased craniofacial cartilage size, chondrocyte size and number, and tended to decrease chondrocyte proliferation, while also causing the Meckel&rsquo;s and palatoquadrate cartilages to be malformed (Burns et al. 2015; Grimes et al. 2008; Liu et al. 2016; Xiong et al. 2008).          Chick embryos exposed to mono-ortho-chlorinated chlorobiphenyls at high concentrations led to mortality of the embryos, with the surviving embryos displaying shortened beaks (as well as microphthalmia, degenerative hepatic lesions and edema) (Brunstrom 1990).         Japanese Quail and Common Pheasant embryos&nbsp;exposed to TCDD,&nbsp;2,3,4,7,8-pentachlorodibenzofuran (PeCDF), and&nbsp;2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzofuran (TCDF), and White Leghorn Chicken embryos exposed to TCDD and PeCDF all displayed bill deformities including incomplete or lack of upper/lower beak or crossbill (Cohen-Barnhouse et al., 2011). Japanese Quail in particular had % deformities that increased in a concentration-depedent manner (0.42 - 23 g/egg) for each chemical.&nbsp;     Some examples for essentiality evidence:    Ahr2 morpholino knockdown in zebrafish exposed to 0.4 ng/mL TCDD provided partial protection from TCDD-induced jaw length shortening (Prasch et al. 2003).     Ahr-null mice were protected from TCDD-induced cleft palate (Mimura et al. 1997).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:47:50 +0000 2026"}